Americans' confidence in the U.S. job market is at its highest level since 2001, with 71% of respondents in May saying it is a good time to find a quality job. This is an improvement from March and April, when 65% rated the job market favorably. The survey was conducted after the Labor Department reported that unemployment in April had fallen to 3.6%, the lowest in nearly 50 years. Additionally, 51% of Americans rate current economic conditions as excellent or good, and 54% say economic conditions are getting better. Overall, Americans' positive perceptions of the economy and the job market have substantially improved compared to the previous decade.